By BO Staff Writer Black First Land First (BLF) President, Andile Mngxitama, met with Ekurhuleni Mayor Mzwandile Masina this morning. Masina took to Twitter today with the message that he is speaking to the BLF President who is also a citizen of Ekurhuleni on the issue of land.  “I just had a very successful meeting with the mayor of my region Cde Mzwandile Masina. We discussed the regions land programme amongst others”, Mngxitama elaborated on social media. Ekurhuleni is the only metro in Gauteng that the ANC managed to secure after the 2016 local government elections. It won the metro by going into coalition with the PAC and AIC. No related posts.